35:44.600 --> 35:46.060
Who has the time?

35:46.143 --> 35:48.354
You really got something.
It's funny.

35:48.437 --> 35:50.690
I didn't understand it at all
till this weekend.

35:50.773 --> 35:53.192
A cooking show?
With her as host?

35:53.276 --> 35:55.319
I don't think we've seen
anything quite like this.

35:55.403 --> 35:58.072
Oh, and Russ,
I spoke with Philly.

35:58.155 --> 36:00.157
Expect a call.
Oh.

36:00.241 --> 36:01.534
Thank you.
Great.

36:01.617 --> 36:04.203
How did you come up
with "The French Chef"?

36:04.287 --> 36:06.622
I mean,
how did you know?

36:06.706 --> 36:08.082
I didn't.

36:08.165 --> 36:10.251
I had no idea.

36:10.334 --> 36:14.338
I think my mother would
have loved "The French Chef."

36:14.422 --> 36:15.923
Oh, Edith
with a television?

36:16.007 --> 36:18.092
Can you imagine?

36:18.175 --> 36:21.971
She was too busy
to sit still long enough.

36:22.054 --> 36:24.765
You know, when she
was bedridden,

36:24.849 --> 36:26.183
I would draw for her,

36:26.267 --> 36:28.853
just so she would have
something to critique.

36:28.936 --> 36:32.481
She lived to deliver
pithy barbs.

36:32.565 --> 36:36.277
My work gave her
ample opportunity.

36:36.360 --> 36:39.614
But I loved her, so...

36:39.697 --> 36:42.617
I'm sorry that I haven't
been able to visit you,

36:42.700 --> 36:44.410
or Robert,
as much as I'd like.

36:44.493 --> 36:47.246
You've always been there
for both of us.

36:47.330 --> 36:50.291
And now Julia's right there
in my living room.

36:50.374 --> 36:51.959
I'm surprised
there has been

36:52.043 --> 36:54.462
such a big response
to the series here.

36:54.545 --> 36:55.713
You shouldn't be.

36:55.796 --> 36:58.966
In San Francisco,
food is everything.

36:59.884 --> 37:03.137
It's one of the things
I love most about this city.

37:04.972 --> 37:08.351
You've departed
to Gloomsville.

37:08.434 --> 37:12.939
Peter is being transferred
to the head office in Chicago.

37:13.022 --> 37:16.651
Promoted, rather.
It's a great opportunity...

37:16.734 --> 37:18.486
But you don't want to leave
San Francisco?

37:18.569 --> 37:22.073
For what?
Pizza pie and Polish sausages?

37:22.156 --> 37:24.408
Polish sausages
are magnificent.

37:24.492 --> 37:26.160
The egg buns
with poppy seeds.

37:26.243 --> 37:27.912
They get stuck
in my teeth.

37:27.995 --> 37:29.330
Ah.

37:29.413 --> 37:30.998
Oh, I am being unfair.

37:31.082 --> 37:33.793
It's his dream,
after all.

37:33.876 --> 37:38.339
But I just wasn't expecting
such upheaval in my life,

37:38.422 --> 37:40.007
not at this age.

37:40.091 --> 37:41.676
I'm settled.

37:41.759 --> 37:44.679
I'm cooked.

37:44.762 --> 37:47.056
Believe me, I understand.

37:47.139 --> 37:48.891
You and Julia moved
all over the world.

37:48.975 --> 37:51.352
That must have been hard,
especially for her.

37:51.435 --> 37:53.229
Oh, she loved it.

37:58.943 --> 38:03.322
Well, I think it's sweet
that you're here supporting her.

38:03.406 --> 38:06.492
I've always admired
you two.

38:06.575 --> 38:10.329
I'm so happy you found her
after Mother passed.

38:16.877 --> 38:19.714
Don't worry
about the move.

38:19.797 --> 38:23.134
The world works
in mysterious ways.

38:23.217 --> 38:25.344
Nothing is predictable.

38:25.428 --> 38:29.181
And the good thing
about love...

38:29.265 --> 38:31.142
is that it travels.

38:33.978 --> 38:37.064
Though, it can be
extremely inconsiderate,

38:37.148 --> 38:39.191
occasionally
self-centered.

38:46.532 --> 38:49.952
It's very kind of you
to escort me home, James.

38:50.036 --> 38:53.205
Thank you for being
my knight in shining armor.

38:53.289 --> 38:54.999
Ken was not very helpful.

38:55.082 --> 38:57.126
The handsome ones
never are.

39:00.755 --> 39:03.549
You know...

39:03.632 --> 39:05.509
I had a cooking show once.

39:05.593 --> 39:07.053
Oh?

39:07.136 --> 39:08.888
I must have been
in France.

39:08.971 --> 39:10.848
Didn't do very well.

39:10.931 --> 39:13.476
Oh, bad timing,
I'm sure.

39:13.559 --> 39:16.771
No.
It wasn't that.

39:16.854 --> 39:22.443
America can't love a fat
old fairy like me.

39:23.944 --> 39:25.905
Oh, James.

39:25.988 --> 39:27.698
No.

39:29.283 --> 39:31.994
You, on the other hand,
make people very happy,

39:32.078 --> 39:33.913
including me.

39:33.996 --> 39:36.957
Now, there's a wonderful
vineyard just outside of Marin

39:37.041 --> 39:38.626
with an unbelievable Syrah,

39:38.709 --> 39:40.461
better than anything
from the Rhone Valley.

39:40.544 --> 39:43.589
It will
knock your socks off.

39:43.672 --> 39:47.802
It is oh-so-tempting,
my darling James,

39:47.885 --> 39:49.178
but I think I have to go.

39:49.261 --> 39:50.513
Yes.
Of course, of course.

39:50.596 --> 39:53.307
Go up and change,
grab Paul, I'll wait.

39:53.390 --> 39:55.393
No, I'm sorry, I can't.

39:58.479 --> 40:01.107
Lucky man, Paul Child.

40:05.027 --> 40:07.029
But you can't shake me
that easily.

40:07.113 --> 40:09.406
Next we'll take on
New York.

40:09.490 --> 40:12.451
Or
even dreary Boston.

40:21.544 --> 40:23.420
Thank you so much.
Thanks, ma'am.
Thank you so much.
Thanks, ma'am.

40:30.719 --> 40:32.096
Where to?

40:32.179 --> 40:34.515
Um...

40:34.598 --> 40:36.475
19th and Diamond Street.

40:44.316 --> 40:46.193
Paul?

40:49.613 --> 40:51.198
Paul, are you here?

40:58.289 --> 41:00.040
Paul?

41:10.009 --> 41:11.552
You're here.

41:14.138 --> 41:15.723
I missed you.

41:15.806 --> 41:17.391
Who are you, again?

41:17.474 --> 41:19.643
Oh, Paul, don't.

41:23.814 --> 41:26.150
I'll freshen up
and then we can go

41:26.233 --> 41:27.943
to the bistro
you mentioned.

41:28.027 --> 41:31.614
Oh, uh, I-I went there
with Claire today.

41:32.615 --> 41:34.533
Oh.

41:34.617 --> 41:36.327
Well,
somewhere else, then.

41:36.410 --> 41:37.870
Mm.

41:37.953 --> 41:40.247
I don't feel
like going out.

41:40.331 --> 41:42.583
On our last night?

41:42.666 --> 41:45.377
Oh, really, Paul,
let's do something.

41:48.839 --> 41:52.343
You were dynamite
on "Good Day by the Bay."

41:52.426 --> 41:55.971
Oh, you watched?
Of course.

41:56.055 --> 41:58.432
I know this weekend wasn't
what we pictured.

41:58.515 --> 42:02.269
I-I got carried away.

42:02.353 --> 42:04.438
Everyone wants you.

42:04.521 --> 42:07.149
And I can hardly
blame them.

42:07.233 --> 42:08.609
I do, too.

42:10.444 --> 42:12.446
Room service?

42:12.529 --> 42:14.114
Oh, yes.

42:14.198 --> 42:15.741
Oh, Paul, are you sure?

42:15.824 --> 42:18.535
Oh, yes.

42:29.046 --> 42:33.384
It's very strange to go from
no one to someone all at once.

42:33.467 --> 42:36.428
I suppose I'll have to
get used to sharing you.

42:36.512 --> 42:38.138
Ooh, split a Caesar?

42:38.222 --> 42:40.224
No, I don't want that.
Oh.

42:40.307 --> 42:42.643
I mean, yes to Caesar,
no to sharing.

42:42.726 --> 42:46.438
No to me being shared,
yes to sharing the salad.

42:46.522 --> 42:48.649
We'll navigate it
together.

42:48.732 --> 42:51.819
See, I don't quite understand
what's happening.

42:51.902 --> 42:53.612
See, I thought it was scary
at first,

42:53.696 --> 42:55.739
I didn't like it,
but now...

42:57.741 --> 42:59.159
...part of me
does like it.

42:59.243 --> 43:00.327
Mm.
A lot.

43:00.411 --> 43:02.705
Mm.
All those people.

43:02.788 --> 43:05.332
It's exciting.

43:05.416 --> 43:08.877
Oh, I can't help it.
Something is happening.

43:08.961 --> 43:11.547
Something is definitely
happening.

43:11.630 --> 43:14.758
But we're still us.

43:14.842 --> 43:16.927
We have to stay us.

43:17.011 --> 43:18.846
Otherwise,
there's no point.

43:18.929 --> 43:21.473
Hm.

43:25.394 --> 43:29.523
Oh, Julie,
they have sole meuniere.

43:32.443 --> 43:34.361
Lovely.
